The paper presents a new data structure for successor search, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. The technical contributions involve efficient single word indices and bit selectors, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the index size, and combinatorics (cs.DM) in the design of the bit selectors. Additionally, the paper involves algorithm design and analysis (cs.AL) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in the analysis of the probe complexity.
